<div><h3>PSCI 154 - Introduction to Public Policy in the United States </h3>  <p><hr>Where do policy ideas originate? How do coalitions form in support or opposition to a policy? Do the dynamics of policy making vary across issues? Focuses on understanding public-policy development and implementation at the national level in the United States, including why some policies fail to develop or why they fail to take effect as intended. Includes assessment of prominent theories of policy development and in-depth analysis of cases. <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=28&coid=93924" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93924&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93924&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt2639" target="_blank">PSCI 050</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>Â strongly recommended.</p>

